trend_summary: Across the image series the township stays largely suburban. Only modest infill housing, a few cul-de-sac extensions and widening of the southeast highway frontage appear. Commercial roofs grow slightly, while forest canopy thickens between streets. No major industrial or high-rise development occurs; land-use change is incremental.
notable_changes: Small residential cul-de-sac clusters added in northern and eastern quarters.
Highway corridor in the southeast gains extra lanes and larger commercial rooftops.
New parking lots and service buildings appear near the central lake-edge campus site.
Tree canopy and green cover become denser along interior streets, indicating maturation or reforestation.
